    - rid: 1264014519372087427
      type: {class: DialogueNode, ns: Dialogue, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        text: Each node you add has a field for text. Note that <b>certain</b> <i>tags</i>
          can be used to change the word styling.
        characterToShow: 2
        jumpIndex: -1
        voice: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 755d0fe9b0b67c441b2051ec604cc269, type: 3}
        onStart:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        onEnd:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        sprite: {fileID: 0}
    - rid: 1264014519372087428
      type: {class: DialogueNode, ns: Dialogue, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        text: 'There is also a <b>Character</b> enum field to indicate who is speakling.


          NOTE:
          you MUST define an option in the <b>ShowLine</b> function of the <b>DialogueManager</b>.
          This is so the UI knows what text to show on the UI.'
        characterToShow: 2
        jumpIndex: -1
        voice: {fileID: 8300000, guid: ba5c5cefbed1a5f41881f147adc9b4f3, type: 3}
        onStart:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        onEnd:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        sprite: {fileID: 0}
    - rid: 1264014519372087431
      type: {class: DialogueNode, ns: Dialogue, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        text: Then, there is a jump index. This indicates which line to show next.
          Negative (default) values simply progress to the next one.
        characterToShow: 2
        jumpIndex: 5
        voice: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 7f426da7824c76449aaf762270cf480b, type: 3}
        onStart:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        onEnd:
          m_PersistentCalls:
            m_Calls: []
        sprite: {fileID: 0}
    - rid: 1264014519372087432
      type: {class: DialogueNode, ns: Dialogue, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
